                <note>
<p>SERIOUS</p>
<p>austerus refers to the gravity natural to an intellectual.</p>
<p>severus refers to gravity as a moral quality.</p>
<p>difficilis refers to someone who does not understand the art of relaxed interaction with other persons, and the word is a pejorative term.</p>
<p>morosus refers to someone who is scrupulous and wants everything to be done according to rule, for want of tolerance.</p>
<p>tetricus refers to a fastidious person who is stiff and constrained from pedantry.</p>
